Manchester United goalkeeper, Joel Pereira has left Old Trafford on a season-long loan to Scottish side, Hearts. Pereira, 23, joined United in 2012 and has made three first-team appearances at Old Trafford. He has also had loan spells with Rochdale, Portuguese clubs: Belenenses and Vitoria Setubal, plus Belgian side, Kortrijk. The goalkeeper will compete with Zdenek Zlamal and Colin Doyle for a starting place at Hearts. Zlamal and Doyle had spells as number one last season, with the former playing all six competitive matches so far this term. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.